Introduction

Base URL: http://localhost

This documentation aims to provide all the information you need to work with our API.

As you scroll, you'll see code examples for working with the API in different programming languages in the dark area to the right (or as part of the content on mobile). You can switch the language used with the tabs at the top right (or from the nav menu at the top left on mobile).

Authenticating requests

This API is not authenticated.

Auth

Login

Make user login

Example request:
curl --request POST \
    "http://localhost/auth" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --data "{
    \"email\": \"marcel83@example.org\",
    \"password\": \"Y|F=c>GHg(i1g\\\\ymyN\"
}"

const url = new URL(
    "http://localhost/auth"
);

const headers = {
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

let body = {
    "email": "marcel83@example.org",
    "password": "Y|F=c>GHg(i1g\\ymyN"
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "POST",
    headers,
    body: JSON.stringify(body),
}).then(response => response.json());

Example response (200):


{
    "data": {
        "id": 1,
        "first_name": "John",
        "last_name": "Week",
        "email": "john@week.com",
        "gender": "m",
        "birth_date": "1997-01-28 00:00:00",
        "token": "5|MIWOec4V5F07kB3iRJWTRMLnPntY1ZqB4O9Yxl5a"
    }
}
Received response:
Request failed with error:

Request      

POST auth

Headers

Content-Type      

Example: application/json

Accept      

Example: application/json

Body Parameters

email   string   

This field must be a valid email address. Example: marcel83@example.org

password   string   

This field must be at least 8 characters. This field must not be greater than 64 characters. Example: Y|F=c>GHg(i1g\ymyN

Logout

Make user logout

Example request:
curl --request GET \
    --get "http://localhost/auth" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json"
const url = new URL(
    "http://localhost/auth"
);

const headers = {
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "GET",
    headers,
}).then(response => response.json());

Example response (200):

Request failed with error:

Endpoints

Return an empty response simply to trigger the storage of the CSRF cookie in the browser.

Example request:
curl --request GET \
    --get "http://localhost/sanctum/csrf-cookie" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json"
const url = new URL(
    "http://localhost/sanctum/csrf-cookie"
);

const headers = {
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "GET",
    headers,
}).then(response => response.json());

GET _ignition/health-check

Example request:
curl --request GET \
    --get "http://localhost/_ignition/health-check" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json"
const url = new URL(
    "http://localhost/_ignition/health-check"
);

const headers = {
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "GET",
    headers,
}).then(response => response.json());
